KZN police have arrested three suspects in possession of 50 Sassa cards and hard cash amounting to R34 000. Police spokeswoman Lieutenant-Colonel Nqobile Gwala said a security official observed suspicious activity at an ATM in Roseneath, Umkomaas, on Friday, 3 June, at about 8.20am. Two women and a man were seen acting suspicious at the ATM and the official decided to join the queue to monitor them. “The suspects had numerous Sassa cards and bank cards that they were using to withdraw cash.” Gwala said the suspects realised that they were being watched and fled in their vehicle. Police officers from Umkomaas cop shop were contacted and the vehicle was monitored. “The suspects moved to another ATM and their vehicle was spotted in the parking lot. The suspects were seen withdrawing money at the ATM. As they returned to their vehicle, police were waiting for them. “Three suspects, aged between 25 and 45, were found with 50 Sassa cards, 20 EasyPay cards and R34 000 cash. “It was established that the suspects had also transferred R360 000 into a private bank account. “All three suspects were arrested for possession of stolen property. More charges are expected to be added. “They are expected to appear in the Scottburgh Magistrates Court tomorrow, 6 June.”